# Test Authentication APIs with Enhanced Duplicate Email Check

## Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5295/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com", 
  "gender": "male",
  "timezone": "America/New_York",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

## Test duplicate email with same case
POST http://localhost:5295/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Another User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "gender": "female",
  "timezone": "Europe/London",
  "password": "differentpassword"
}

###

## Test duplicate email with different case (should still fail)
POST http://localhost:5295/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Case Test User",
  "email": "TEST@EXAMPLE.COM",
  "gender": "other",
  "timezone": "Asia/Tokyo",
  "password": "anotherpassword"
}

###

## Test duplicate email with extra spaces (should still fail)
POST http://localhost:5295/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Space Test User",
  "email": "  test@example.com  ",
  "gender": "male",
  "timezone": "Australia/Sydney",
  "password": "spacepassword"
}

###

## Login with the user (case insensitive)
POST http://localhost:5295/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "TEST@EXAMPLE.COM",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

## Test invalid login
POST http://localhost:5295/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "wrong@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}
